description:
Sources: https://sites.google.com/view/sources-argentine-ants

In nearly every corner of the Earth, ants wage war against each other. Their weapons are what nature gave them. Some have strong armour, deadly stingers or sharp mandibles. And then there is this tiny, and not very impressive ant. But it rules the biggest empire any ant has ever built. A colony spanning continents and fighting wars that leave  millions of casualties. Lets take a look at this unlikely warrioress: Linepithema humile, the Argentine ant.
